## Step 4: Rewrite the sum $S$ using the expression for $F_{n+2}$ in terms of $F_{n+1}$ and $F_n$
\begin{align*}
S &= \sum_{n = 1}^\infty \frac{F_{n + 1}}{F_n F_{n + 2}} \\
&= \sum_{n = 1}^\infty \frac{F_{n + 1}}{F_n (F_{n+1} + F_n)}
\end{align*}

## Step 5: Notice that this is a telescoping series
The given series can be rewritten as follows:
\begin{align*}
\sum_{n = 1}^\infty \left(\frac{1}{F_n} - \frac{1}{F_{n+1} + F_n}\right) &= \lim_{n \to \infty} \sum_{k = 1}^{n - 1} \left(\frac{1}{F_k} - \frac{1}{F_{k + 1} + F_k}\right) \\
&= \lim_{n \to \infty} \left(\frac{1}{F_1} - \frac{1}{F_{n + 1} + F_n}\right).
\end{align*}

## Step 3: Simplify the series
\begin{align*}
\sum_{n = 1}^\infty \frac{F_{n + 1}}{F_n F_{n + 2}} &= \frac{F_{2}}{F_1 F_{3}} + \frac{F_{3}}{F_2 F_{4}} + \frac{F_{4}}{F_3 F_{5}} + \cdots \\
&= \frac{1}{F_1 F_2} + \frac{1}{F_2 F_3} + \frac{1}{F_3 F_4} + \cdots
\end{align*}
